  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Recruitment Manager",
  "description": "<p><strong>About the role:</strong><br />We are looking for passionate individuals and experienced recruiters to join our team as <strong>Recruitment Manager / Assistant Manager.</strong></p><p><br /><em><strong>What we offer:</strong></em></p><p><ul><li>Basic Salary $3000 to $3500, with <strong>uncapped Monthly Commission.</strong></li><li>Career progression</li><li>Flexi-work arrangement </li></ul></p><p><em><strong>What you will do:</strong></em></p><p><ul><li>Drive sales results through proactive client sourcing, precise candidate matching, and consistent placement closures.</li><li>Manage the full recruitment cycle, from job postings to offers, ensuring efficient and timely hiring processes.</li><li>Partner with BD Team and hiring managers to understand the specific hiring needs and job requirements.</li><li>Proactively source candidates through various channels, including social media and networking, to build a strong pool of talent.</li><li>Review resumes, engage with potential candidates, and ensure a good match for each role.</li><li>Maintain clear and open communication with hiring managers to keep them updated on sourcing progress.</li><li>Provide regular, timely reports on sourcing activity and results, ensuring alignment with hiring targets.</li><li>Tracks and meets hiring targets, with an emphasis on quality and timely placement.</li><li>Foster a positive candidate experience throughout the sourcing process.</li><li>Contribute ideas to improve sourcing strategies and candidate engagement.</li><li>Perform any other duties as assigned by the Department Manager.</li></ul></p><p><em><strong>Requirements:</strong></em></p><p><ul><li>\"O\" or \"A\" Level, Diploma or Degree (in any discipline) from recognized institutions</li><li>Possessed at least two to three years of talent acquisition or recruitment experience</li><li>A friendly and outgoing personality</li><li>Self-driven, great problem-solving skills, attention to details</li></ul></p>",
